<br>
I guess I'm an idealist. I watch the movies, and there's a guy with a sword in each hand who wins an entire fight because he's got the guts to lead a charge against the back line, or smack the big guy in order to rescue the weaker friend, and he almost dies, then doesnt.<br>
<br>
But we can't do any of this stuff. I stopped seeing myself as a living entity on the battlefield because of the hundreds of times I died within the space of one second and the times I've been raped by MOC after going through the hell of burning IP on that DoT, burning Flurrry on that caster, burning Purge on that Shieldo and being CC'd again by something else, or just PBAE'd into oblivion in 2 hits.<br>
<br>
So get this straight- AOE abilities and long-range casting/CC, versus the ability to run toward the enemy and hit them when you get there. But you can't give the enemy caster &quot;no chance&quot; (I mean what if his slam bot is a bad player? Who's gonna protect him?) so they get MOC/lifetap or PBAE or a hundred pets that nuke you for 500 a time. It hurts knowing that you're a thousand realm points.<br>
<br>
I now see my Mercenary as a non-insta spell that wanders around the battlefield. If I was a nuke that might be OK, though polearmsmen tell me it's not. If I was a targetted stun I might enjoy it, though my guild Paladin tells me it's not. But I'm sure that, after playing my tank for longer than any of the guys in my guild, that being a slammable minor DoT is about as worthless as you can feel in a fight that lasts &quot;a couple of ticks&quot;.<br>
<br>
Hord's unofficial Berzerker TL report had a footnote about giving something back to melee classes. At the moment they are giving casters more and more abilities that melee classes simple can't have because they are suposed to be classes of simplicity. Hell, they're even giving casters some decent Melee abilities.<br>
<br>
Reaver or Infiltrator... what would you pick? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lemonade@lighttanksofdaoc>Lemonade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/relic/Xid.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#000000>(7/1/03 8:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=274.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: getting used to it</span><hr size=1> Blame that is exactly how I feel and this class is nothing more than just an inf with less evade, chain, parry, but no CS and stealth. They prevail because they have a better chance of survival and can solo in RVR where as WE CAN NOT and depend on groups which we offer little value to groups so it is hard to get one and is usually a &quot;pickup&quot; group. It is such a shame to say such things and people get mad about it but IT IS THE TRUTH.<br>
