<br>
The Reaver will function the same way you function with your merc. Go after casters and support (pretty much, no tank is ever suppose to go against another tank. Weird, but that seems to be the way it goes). He's over-all better, PvE and RvR. He does more damage, and has a shield for more group-ability (doesn't take all that much damage either, aswell as replace whatever health he lost with procs or that lifetap). Pretty much, whatever you wanted from your merc, the reaver will give. Just goes about it in a different fashion. You'll be able to pwn infs with that AOE, since you have a good chance to uncover 'em, while dealing great damage at an acceptable rate (assuming you're going flexable).<br>
<br>
I also share(d) your thought on the merc. I always think in terms of &quot;If I deal enough damage fast enough, I can kill without having to worry about Defense. The flip side, if i'm ever forbidden from reaching my target, i'm open for an easy kill&quot;. As it stands, the last part remains true, and even when i'm next to and hitting my target, I still end up dead most of the time. The problem as I see it, we're just not doing enough damage. I MUST have another person /assisting me in order to do what, say, a polearmsman could in the same situation.<br>
<br>
All we need is an increase to our damage. I don't care how, a direct increase or increase our growth rates on Duel Wield to do Advanced Spec Damage. Either one, I just need more damage output besides flurry and what I do now. The whole Damage Over Time theory is non exsistant in RvR today. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
