/agrees with Fingoniel<br>
<br>
If yer in a pick-up group, expect to be owned, doesn't matter what class you are, any decent guild group will wipe you flat.  As will a zerg, either one of which you're more likely to run into in Emain than another pick-up group, as they've already been wiped by the zerg/guild groups by the time you would have gotten to them.  Sorry, but without decent planning on the make-up of a group that's what's most likely to happen.<br>
<br>
Want good action, take the time to get a solid group together, make sure everyone understands their roles, and go into the Mid or Alb frontiers, that's where you're most likely to find a good small group encounter, and also where you'll notice your effectiveness increase, especially if you have a polearmsman assisting off you, or if you're working with a Slam tank against a caster/healer.<br>
<br>
Make sure you're playing smart, charging into the back ranks of casters isn't necessarily the best approach, try staying closer to the middle lines, staying in range of your healer (will make for a MUCH less frustrated healer-trust me).  Take out support, hopefully you've got some sort of CC to deal with their casters. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
