The healers I was referring to killing was obviously in enemy groups. I used to love killing mid healers. My own method of handling RvR (mind I'm not playing a 50 these days. I got mad one day and hit delete.) has always been assist if possible. If not head for the closest finger waggler you can find with healers high on the list. But if I happen to see someone holding a musical instrument, they're fair game too. <br>
<br>
My point was that tanks are rarely your target of choice. <br>
<br>
Battles are too short but if you're equipped right and have the right RAs in a good group, they last long enough to do some damage. If they're not for you, I'd take a good hard look at those factors to figure out why.<br>
